Updating data with PyMongo

	update_one, update_many and replace_one. 

	The update_one method will update a single document based on a query that matches a document.

CRUD operations create, read, update, and delete documents.

create
	 
	 db.collection.insertOne() 
	 db.collection.insertMany()

Read
	
	db.collection.find()

Update

	db.collection.updateOne() 
	db.collection.updateMany() 
	db.collection.replaceOne()

Delete 
	
	db.collection.deleteOne() 
	db.collection.deleteMany()

bulkWrite()

bulkWrite() supports the following write operations:

	insertOne
	updateOne
	updateMany
	replaceOne
	deleteOne
	deleteMany